You look out the window.
<?php
$d = date("m");

if ($d < "3") {
  echo "You see frost everywhere, and a dusting of snow.";
} elseif ($d < "6") {
  echo "It's a lovely shade of green outside, and sopping wet; good for flowers, bad for dry clothes.";
} elseif ($d < "9") {
  echo "It's quite hot. You hope your air conditioner can keep up with your desire not to melt.";
} elseif ($d < "12") {
  echo "The leaves are turning the outside world into a fiesta of color as cold and hot weather battle it out for ultimate dominion.";
}


?>
 Also,

<?php
$t = date("H");

if ($t < "6") {
  echo "it's too early for the sun. Why are you up?";
} elseif ($t < "9") {
  echo "it's breakfast time.";
} elseif ($t < "11") {
  echo "it's been ages since breakfast, and a while until lunch. Time for a little something.";
} elseif ($t < "13") {
  echo "it's lunch time.";
} elseif ($t < "15") {
  echo "it's that time after lunch when you start to get a little drowsy.";
} elseif ($t < "18") {
  echo "it's that time in the afternoon where you start thinking about dinner, and how tired you are, and coffee.";
} elseif ($t < "20") {
  echo "it's dinner time, and boy are you hungry.";
} elseif ($t < "23") {
  echo "it's beginning to be sort of late in the evening, and it's been a long day.";
} else {
  echo "it's quite late now.";
}



echo " You need some coffee."

